name: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Respondent v. Darius PETERSON, Petitioner

parties: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Respondent v. Darius PETERSON, Petitioner.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 21st day of September, 2011, the Petition for Allowance of Appeal is GRANTED. The issue, as stated by Petitioner, is:
Is the Superior Court’s decision denying Petitioner’s Rule 600 claim directly contrary to well-settled precedent established by this Court?
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

29 A.3d 368
COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Respondent v. Darius PETERSON, Petitioner.

Sept. 21, 2011.
